cadL2vpnMIB.name: cadL2vpnMIB

revisions.description: Changed mib object name from cadL2vpnInterfaceIpMcastFwdToCpeEnabled to cadL2vpnInterfaceIpIgmpSnooping
Changed the MAX-ACCESS of cadL2vpnInterfaceIpMcastFwdToCpeEnabled from read-write to read-create
Added cadL2vpnDenyForwardingMplsPeerIp to cadL2vpnDenyForwardingEntry. Added cadL2vpnMplsPeerIpToCmTable
Remove cadL2vpnCmToInstanceIdTable and cadL2vpnCmStatsTable. Added cerL2vpnCmVpnIdTable and cerL2vpnCmStatsTable. Added cadL2vpnInstanceIdVpnId to cadL2vpnInstanceIdToCmEntry
change syntax of cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeNsiEncapSubtype to read-create.
rename cadl2vpnInstanceVlanId to cadL2vpnInstanceVpnId. rename cadL2vpnVlanIdx to cadL2vpnVpnIdx.
add cadL2vpnDenyForwardingTable, change syntax of cadL2vpnCmForwardingEnabled from read-write to read-only change cadL2vpnCmStatsEntry to cadL2vpnCmStatusEntry

cadL2vpnMIB.contactinfo: Arris Technical Support Postal: ARRIS E-Mail: support@arrisi.com
cadL2vpnMIB.description: This is the management MIB contains Cadant proprietary L2VPN MIB information. Copyright 2009 Arris International, Inc. All rights reserved.

CadNsiEncapValue.name: CadNsiEncapValue
CadNsiEncapValue.description: The encapsulation value for L2VPN forwarded packets on NSI ports. The value of an object of this type depends on the value of an associated object of type DocsEncapSubtype: other(1): vendor specific, ieee8021q(2): 802.1Q tag with VLAN ID in lower 12 bits, ieee8021ad(3): pair of 12-bit values with service provider in 12 most significant bits of the 24-bit value and customer VLAN ID in the 12 least significant bits of the 24-bit value, mpls(4): must be zero length string, l2tpv3(5): must be zero length string.

cadL2vpnPrimaryNetworkIfIndex.name: cadL2vpnPrimaryNetworkIfIndex
cadL2vpnPrimaryNetworkIfIndex.description: ifIndex of the primary physical netowrk interface used for L2VPN traffic. Zero if no primary L2VPN network interface is configured.

cadL2vpnSecondaryNetworkIfIndex.name: cadL2vpnSecondaryNetworkIfIndex
cadL2vpnSecondaryNetworkIfIndex.description: ifIndex of the secondary physical netowrk interface used for L2VPN traffic. Zero if no secondary L2VPN network interface is configured.

cadL2vpnActiveNetworkIfIndex.name: cadL2vpnActiveNetworkIfIndex
cadL2vpnActiveNetworkIfIndex.description: ifIndex of the currently active physical netowrk interface being used for L2VPN traffic. Zero if no active L2VPN network interface is up.

cadL2vpnForwardingEnabled.name: cadL2vpnForwardingEnabled
cadL2vpnForwardingEnabled.description: The global L2VPN forwarding state. The default is false(2).

cadL2vpnCmCapEsafeIdentRequired.name: cadL2vpnCmCapEsafeIdentRequired
cadL2vpnCmCapEsafeIdentRequired.description: When true eSAFE identity TLVs are required in REG-REQ message otherwise the CM registration will be rejected if L2VPN TLVs are present. When false a CM may register without these capability TLVs.

cadL2vpnCmCapDutFilterRequired.name: cadL2vpnCmCapDutFilterRequired
cadL2vpnCmCapDutFilterRequired.description: When true Downstream Unencrypted Traffic (DUT) filter capability TLV is required in REG-REQ message, otherwise the CM registration will be rejected if L2VPN TLVs are present. When false a CM may register without this capability TLV.

cadL2vpnInterfaceTable.name: cadL2vpnInterfaceTable
cadL2vpnInterfaceTable.description: L2VPN interface table contains an entry for each cable MAC interface declared for use with L2VPNs.

cadL2vpnInterfaceEntry.name: cadL2vpnInterfaceEntry
cadL2vpnInterfaceEntry.description: each interface must be a unique DOCSIS 3.0 cable MAC interface

cadL2vpnInterfaceIfIndex.name: cadL2vpnInterfaceIfIndex
cadL2vpnInterfaceIfIndex.description: Cable MAC layer ifIndex for this interface.

cadL2vpnInterfaceIpIgmpSnooping.name: cadL2vpnInterfaceIpIgmpSnooping
cadL2vpnInterfaceIpIgmpSnooping.description: If set to true(1), this attribute enables the L2VPN IGMP Snooping feature on this cable-mac interface. If set to false(2), this attribute disables the L2VPN IGMP Snooping feature on this cable-mac interface. The default is false(2).

cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeTable.name: cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeTable
cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeTable.description: VPN VLANid range table. Contains ranges of outer VLANids declared for use with L2VPNs and L3VPNs.

cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeEntry.name: cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeEntry
cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeEntry.description: contain a VPN VLANid range entry

cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeEnd.name: cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeEnd
cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeEnd.description: End range of VLANid. Must be greater than or equal to cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeBegin.

cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeNsiEncapSubtype.name: cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeNsiEncapSubtype
cadL2vpnVlanIdRangeNsiEncapSubtype.description: NSI Encapsulation subtype of the VLANid.

cadL2vpnInstanceId.name: cadL2vpnInstanceId
cadL2vpnInstanceId.description: The 24-bit L2VPN instance identifier composed from 2 12-bit VLANids assigned to the L2VPN instance.

cadL2vpnInstanceIdVlanIdOuter.name: cadL2vpnInstanceIdVlanIdOuter
cadL2vpnInstanceIdVlanIdOuter.description: Outer VLANid of this L2VPN Instance.

cadL2vpnInstanceIdVlanIdInner.name: cadL2vpnInstanceIdVlanIdInner
cadL2vpnInstanceIdVlanIdInner.description: Inner VLANid of this L2VPN Instance.

cadL2vpnInstanceIdCmMac.name: cadL2vpnInstanceIdCmMac
cadL2vpnInstanceIdCmMac.description: CM MAC address of this L2VPN Instance.

cadL2vpnInstanceIdVpnId.name: cadL2vpnInstanceIdVpnId
cadL2vpnInstanceIdVpnId.description: VPN ID of this L2VPN Instance.

cadL2vpnIdxToCmVpnInstTable.name: cadL2vpnIdxToCmVpnInstTable
cadL2vpnIdxToCmVpnInstTable.description: This table contains all the VPN instances ordered by VPN Index, CM MAC and VPN Instance ID.

cadL2vpnVpnIdx.name: cadL2vpnVpnIdx
cadL2vpnVpnIdx.description: An internally assigned index value for a known VLAD ID. Refer docsL2vpnIdx.

cadL2vpnPktClassTable.name: cadL2vpnPktClassTable
cadL2vpnPktClassTable.description: This table provides the L2VPN-specific objects for packet classifiers that apply to only L2VPN traffic. The indices of this table are a subset of the indices of classifiers in docsQosPktClassTable.

cadL2vpnPktClassEntry.name: cadL2vpnPktClassEntry
cadL2vpnPktClassEntry.description: An entry in this table extends a single row of docsQosPktClassTable for a rule that applies only to downstream L2VPN forwarded packets. The index ifIndex is an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127).

cadL2vpnPktClassL2vpnId.name: cadL2vpnPktClassL2vpnId
cadL2vpnPktClassL2vpnId.description: The locally assigned L2VPN index corresponding to the VPN Identifier subtype of a Downstream Classifier L2VPN Encoding.

cadL2vpnPktClassUserPriRangeLow.name: cadL2vpnPktClassUserPriRangeLow
cadL2vpnPktClassUserPriRangeLow.description: The lower priority of the user Priority Range subtype of a Downstream Classifier L2VPN Encoding. If the subtype was omitted, this object has value 0.

cadL2vpnPktClassUserPriRangeHigh.name: cadL2vpnPktClassUserPriRangeHigh
cadL2vpnPktClassUserPriRangeHigh.description: The higher priority of the user Priority Range subtype of a Downstream Classifier L2VPN Encoding. If the subtype was omitted, this object has value 7.

cadL2vpnPktClassCMIM.name: cadL2vpnPktClassCMIM
cadL2vpnPktClassCMIM.description: The Cable Modem Interface Mask (CMIM) signaled in a Packet Classifier Encoding. In a Downstream Packet Classifier Encoding, a specified CMIM value restricts the classifier to match packets with a Destination MAC address corresponding to the interfaces indicated in the CMIM mask. The eCM self and any eSAFE interface bits correspond to the individual eCM and eSAFE host MAC addresses. In an Upstream Packet Classifier encoding, a specified CMIM value restricts the classifier to match packets with an ingress bridge port interface matching the bits in the CMIM value. If the CMIM subtype was omitted, this object should be reported as a zero length octet string.

cadL2vpnPktClassVendorSpecific.name: cadL2vpnPktClassVendorSpecific
cadL2vpnPktClassVendorSpecific.description: This object provides the set of configured Vendor Specific subtypes within a Packet Classifier Encoding for a CM. If no Vendor Specific subtype was specified, this object is a zero length octet string. If one or more Vendor Specific subtype parameters was specified, this object represents the concatenation of all such subtypes.

cadL2vpnDenyForwardingTable.name: cadL2vpnDenyForwardingTable
cadL2vpnDenyForwardingTable.description: This table provides the L2VPN-specific deny data forwarding list. The index of this table is an arbitrary number.

cadL2vpnDenyForwardingEntry.name: cadL2vpnDenyForwardingEntry
cadL2vpnDenyForwardingEntry.description: An entry in this table can be a VPN Id, CM MAC or VLAN id. When a row is created or removed, SCM will set the associated VLANid cadL2vpnCmForwardingEnabled to true(1) or false(2).

cadL2vpnDenyForwardingVpnId.name: cadL2vpnDenyForwardingVpnId
cadL2vpnDenyForwardingVpnId.description: When it is specified, data forwarding of all the VLANid within this VPN ID will be disabled.

cadL2vpnDenyForwardingInstanceId.name: cadL2vpnDenyForwardingInstanceId
cadL2vpnDenyForwardingInstanceId.description: When it is specified, data forwarding of this VLAN instance will be disabled.

cadL2vpnDenyForwardingCmMac.name: cadL2vpnDenyForwardingCmMac
cadL2vpnDenyForwardingCmMac.description: When it is specified, data forwarding of all the VLANid within this CM will be disabled.

cadL2vpnDenyForwardingRowStatus.name: cadL2vpnDenyForwardingRowStatus
cadL2vpnDenyForwardingRowStatus.description: row status of this table entry.

cadL2vpnDenyForwardingMplsPeerIp.name: cadL2vpnDenyForwardingMplsPeerIp
cadL2vpnDenyForwardingMplsPeerIp.description: When it is specified, data forwarding of all the L2VPN Instances that have MPLS PW going to this peer will be disabled

cerL2vpnCmVpnIdEntry.name: cerL2vpnCmVpnIdEntry
cerL2vpnCmVpnIdEntry.description: An entry is indexed by Cable Modem MAC address and L2VPN VPN ID.

cerL2vpnCmMac.name: cerL2vpnCmMac
cerL2vpnCmMac.description: The CM MAC address hosting this this L2VPN Instance.

cerL2vpnCmVpnId.name: cerL2vpnCmVpnId
cerL2vpnCmVpnId.description: An externally configured octet string that identifies an L2VPN.

cerL2vpnCmNsiEncapSubtype.name: cerL2vpnCmNsiEncapSubtype
cerL2vpnCmNsiEncapSubtype.description: The General Encapsulation Information (GEI) subtype of the Network System Interface (NSI) encapsulation configured for the CM.

cerL2vpnIdx.name: cerL2vpnIdx
cerL2vpnIdx.description: An internally assigned index value for a known VLAD ID. Refer docsL2vpnIdx.

cerL2vpnCmForwardingEnabled.name: cerL2vpnCmForwardingEnabled
cerL2vpnCmForwardingEnabled.description: L2VPN forwarding state for all L2VPN instances hosted by this CM and VLAN instance.

cerL2vpnInstanceId.name: cerL2vpnInstanceId
cerL2vpnInstanceId.description: The 24-bit L2VPN instance identifier composed from 2 12-bit VLANids assigned to the L2VPN instance.

cerL2vpnCmCompliantCapability.name: cerL2vpnCmCompliantCapability
cerL2vpnCmCompliantCapability.description: Whether an L2VPN CM is compliant with DOCSIS specification. Refer docsL2vpnCmCompliantCapability.

cerL2vpnCmDutFilteringCapability.name: cerL2vpnCmDutFilteringCapability
cerL2vpnCmDutFilteringCapability.description: Whether an L2VPN forwarding CM is capable of Downstream Unencrypted Traffic(DUT) Filtering. Refer docsL2vpnCmDutFilteringCapability.

cerL2vpnCmDutCMIM.name: cerL2vpnCmDutCMIM
cerL2vpnCmDutCMIM.description: Reports the value in a per-CM L2VPN Encoding for DUT Cable Modem Interface Mask(CMIM).

cerL2vpnCmDhcpSnooping.name: cerL2vpnCmDhcpSnooping
cerL2vpnCmDhcpSnooping.description: Reports the value of the Enable DHCP Snooping subtype of a top-level L2VPN Encoding.

cerL2vpnVpnCmCMIM.name: cerL2vpnVpnCmCMIM
cerL2vpnVpnCmCMIM.description: A Cable Modem Interface Mask represents a set of MAC bridge interfaces within the CM.

cerL2vpnVpnCmIndividualSAID.name: cerL2vpnVpnCmIndividualSAID
cerL2vpnVpnCmIndividualSAID.description: The BPI+ Security Association ID in which traffic intended for point-to-point forwarding through an individual CM is forwarded. If the CMTS does not allocate an individual SAID for multipoint forwarding (as is recommended),it MUST report this object as zero.

cerL2vpnVpnCmVendorSpecific.name: cerL2vpnVpnCmVendorSpecific
cerL2vpnVpnCmVendorSpecific.description: This object encodes the concatenation of all Vendor Specific Subtype encodings that appeared in any registration per-CM L2VPN Encoding associated with this entry.

cerL2vpnCmNsiEncapValue.name: cerL2vpnCmNsiEncapValue
cerL2vpnCmNsiEncapValue.description: The encapsulation value for L2VPN forwarded packets on NSI ports.

cerL2vpnMplsAcId.name: cerL2vpnMplsAcId
cerL2vpnMplsAcId.description: The 20 bit value of the MPLS AC ID. Assigned by the the UCAM. Has to be unique within a CMTS chassis.

cerL2vpnCmMplsPwId.name: cerL2vpnCmMplsPwId
cerL2vpnCmMplsPwId.description: This is the MPLS PW ID (4byte long non-zero).

cerL2vpnCmMplsPeerAddrType.name: cerL2vpnCmMplsPeerAddrType
cerL2vpnCmMplsPeerAddrType.description: This is the MPLS Peer Address Type. Only IPv4(1) or IPv6(2) will be supported. unknown(0) ipv4(1) ipv6(2) ipv4z(3) ipv6z(4) dns(16)

cerL2vpnCmMplsPeerAddr.name: cerL2vpnCmMplsPeerAddr
cerL2vpnCmMplsPeerAddr.description: This is the IP address of the MPLS Peer. IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are supported.

cerL2vpnCmBgpVpnId.name: cerL2vpnCmBgpVpnId
cerL2vpnCmBgpVpnId.description: This is the BGP VPN ID for L2VPN with BGP auto-discovery and LDP signaling (4byte long non-zero).

cerL2vpnCmBgpRd.name: cerL2vpnCmBgpRd
cerL2vpnCmBgpRd.description: BGP Route Distinguisher for L2VPN BGP auto-discovery (8 bytes long)

cerL2vpnCmBgpRtImport.name: cerL2vpnCmBgpRtImport
cerL2vpnCmBgpRtImport.description: BGP Route Target Import for L2VPN BGP auto-discovery (8 bytes long)

cerL2vpnCmBgpRtExport.name: cerL2vpnCmBgpRtExport
cerL2vpnCmBgpRtExport.description: BGP Route Target Export for L2VPN BGP auto-discovery (8 bytes long)

cerL2vpnCmBgpCeVeId.name: cerL2vpnCmBgpCeVeId
cerL2vpnCmBgpCeVeId.description: This is the 2 byte long CE-ID/VE-ID for L2VPN with BGP auto-discovery and signaling.

cerL2vpnCmStatsTable.name: cerL2vpnCmStatsTable
cerL2vpnCmStatsTable.description: This table is used to populate data to docsL2vpnCmStatusEntry.

cerL2vpnCmStatsEntry.name: cerL2vpnCmStatsEntry
cerL2vpnCmStatsEntry.description: An entry is indexed by Cable Modem MAC address and VPN ID.

cerL2vpnCmStatsUpstreamPkts.name: cerL2vpnCmStatsUpstreamPkts
cerL2vpnCmStatsUpstreamPkts.description: The number of L2vpn-forwarded packets received from this instance's Cable Modem on this instance's L2VPN.

cerL2vpnCmStatsUpstreamBytes.name: cerL2vpnCmStatsUpstreamBytes
cerL2vpnCmStatsUpstreamBytes.description: The number of L2vpn-forwarded bytes received from this instance's Cable Modem on this instance's L2VPN.

cerL2vpnCmStatsUpstreamDiscards.name: cerL2vpnCmStatsUpstreamDiscards
cerL2vpnCmStatsUpstreamDiscards.description: The number of L2-forwarded packets discarded from this instance's Cable Modem on this instance's VPN.

cerL2vpnCmStatsDownstreamPkts.name: cerL2vpnCmStatsDownstreamPkts
cerL2vpnCmStatsDownstreamPkts.description: The number of L2-forwarded packets transmitted to this instance's Cable Modem on this instance's VPN.

cerL2vpnCmStatsDownstreamBytes.name: cerL2vpnCmStatsDownstreamBytes
cerL2vpnCmStatsDownstreamBytes.description: The number of L2-forwarded bytes transmitted to this instance's Cable Modem on this instance's VPN.

cerL2vpnCmStatsDownstreamDiscards.name: cerL2vpnCmStatsDownstreamDiscards
cerL2vpnCmStatsDownstreamDiscards.description: The number of L2-forwarded packets that were discarded before they could be transmitted to this instance's Cable Modem on this instance's VPN.

cadL2vpnMplsPeerIpToCmTable.name: cadL2vpnMplsPeerIpToCmTable
cadL2vpnMplsPeerIpToCmTable.description: This table contains all MPLS L2VPN instances with no auto-discovery ordered by MPLS Peer IP, CM MAC and VPN ID.

cerL2vpnCmMplsPeerIpAddress.name: cerL2vpnCmMplsPeerIpAddress
cerL2vpnCmMplsPeerIpAddress.description: This is the IP address of the MPLS Peer. IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are supported.

cadL2vpnProvisionedCmTable.name: cadL2vpnProvisionedCmTable
cadL2vpnProvisionedCmTable.description: This table contains all CMs that are statically provisioned with L2VPNs.

cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEntry.name: cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEntry
cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEntry.description: An entry contains a CM that is statically provisioned with L2VPNs. The CM MAC address is the unique key to an entry.

cadL2vpnProvisionedCmMacAddress.name: cadL2vpnProvisionedCmMacAddress
cadL2vpnProvisionedCmMacAddress.description: The CM MAC address used as a unique key to this table.

cadL2vpnProvisionedCmL2vpnId.name: cadL2vpnProvisionedCmL2vpnId
cadL2vpnProvisionedCmL2vpnId.description: The provisioned CM's string form of the L2VPNid.

cadL2vpnProvisionedCmOuterVlanId.name: cadL2vpnProvisionedCmOuterVlanId
cadL2vpnProvisionedCmOuterVlanId.description: The provisoned CM's L2VPN outer VLAN id.

cadL2vpnProvisionedCmInnerVlanId.name: cadL2vpnProvisionedCmInnerVlanId
cadL2vpnProvisionedCmInnerVlanId.description: The provisoned CM's L2VPN inner VLAN id.

cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEsafeTable.name: cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEsafeTable
cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEsafeTable.description: This table contains all eSAFE devices that are statically provisioned behind a CM that are excluded from the L2VPN tunnel. This MIB is maintained by the CLI commands.

cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEsafeEntry.name: cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEsafeEntry
cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEsafeEntry.description: An entry contains a Esafe device that is statically provisioned behind a CM that is excluded from the L2VPN tunnel.

cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEsafeMacAddress.name: cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEsafeMacAddress
cadL2vpnProvisionedCmEsafeMacAddress.description: The eSAFE MAC address used as a key to this table.
